hurt his feelings.

43:56.051 --> 43:57.845
Very pleased to meet you,
Michael.

43:57.970 --> 44:00.180
I hope you'll be my friend.

44:00.305 --> 44:02.349
Father, are you staying?

44:05.185 --> 44:08.397
Children, I've been gone
far too long,

44:08.522 --> 44:11.567
so I've brought you
this special treat!

44:19.950 --> 44:21.994
Suppertime.

44:22.119 --> 44:24.329
[Children growling]

44:32.254 --> 44:34.131
Sugar Plum...

44:35.757 --> 44:37.217
...aren't you hungry?

44:37.342 --> 44:40.512
- You promised me you'd stay.
- CHARLIE: Uh-uh.

44:40.637 --> 44:43.765
I promised you I would never
let the lights go out again.

44:44.933 --> 44:47.269
And I intend to
keep that promise.

44:47.394 --> 44:49.938
But we mustn't be selfish.

44:50.063 --> 44:53.192
Think of all the children
who need saving.

44:53.317 --> 44:55.027
Now more than ever.

44:55.152 --> 44:57.196
You understand that.

44:57.321 --> 44:58.989
You're a big girl now.

45:00.490 --> 45:02.826
I will be back...

45:04.119 --> 45:06.747
...just as soon as I can.

45:06.872 --> 45:09.499
[Children growling]

45:11.251 --> 45:14.963
[ Car door opens, closes]

45:25.474 --> 45:30.479
This is the one,
isn't it, Mr. Manx?

45:30.604 --> 45:33.607
I knew it when I saw it,
just like you said.

45:33.732 --> 45:36.610
We must save him,
Bing Partridge.

45:36.735 --> 45:38.946
- Don't you agree?
- Ah, yeah.

